olive oil
3 clove garlic
20 g butter
1 onion
1 packet Chopped Veggie Mix
½ packet tomato paste
1 tin Coconut Cream
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet basmati rice
1.5 cup water (for the rice)
1 packet pulled beef
1 sachet Sri Lankan spice blend
½ cup water (for the curry)

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, melt the butter with a dash of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook 1/2 the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add basmati rice, water(for the rice) and a pinch of salt and bring to the boil. Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid. Cook for 10 minutes, then remove from the heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and the water has absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, finely chop brown onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook onion and chopped veggie mix, stirring occasionally, until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a bowl.

• Drain liquid from pulled beef.
• Return frying pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook Sri Lankan spice blend and tomato paste (see ingredients) until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add pulled beef and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until warmed through, 1-2 minutes. Add water(for the curry), coconut cream and beef-style stock powder and stir to combine.
• Return veggies to frying pan with the beef. Add baby spinach leaves, then season with salt and cook until thickened, 2-3 minutes.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls.
• Top with Sri Lankan pulled beef and veggie curry.
• Sprinkle with crushed peanuts.